Req. ID: 292681 
Responsibilities and Tasks include the following, but not limited to: 
Owning the development of a new memory & emerging memory modules. 
Lead a cross Micron team in the development of all elements of the aforementioned module solutions. 
Lead the interaction with the business teams and end customers for the responsible products. 
Qualifications: 
10+ years of shown experience leading system architecture and medium sized technical teams. 
BS/MS/PhD in Electrical Engineering, Microelectronics, Computer Science or related field 
Knowledge of PCIe, Server Platforms (BIOS, ACPI, RAS) 
Knowledge of memory controllers 
Knowledge of ASIC development and system simulation 
Knowledge of systems performance analysis to craft strategy and products 
Working level expertise in Cloud Systems and qualification process 
Ability to provide leadership in technical areas outside immediate background, such as: 
System Security Architecture 
Hardware to Firmware Interfaces 
System Management Architecture (In Band, Out of Band) 
Media Management Architecture 
Power and Thermal Management 
Debug DFT/DFX Architectures 
Software Architecture in the Linux and Windows environments. 
